attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Renesas SH, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This RISC-V ELF binary is a malicious IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai or Satori families. It contains an embedded exploit payload targeting the Huawei HG532 remote code execution vulnerability (CVE-2017-17215), as evidenced by strings related to 'DeviceUpgrade_1', 'HuaweiHomeGateway', and SOAP/UPnP XML structures containing command injection sequences. The malware also exhibits typical botnet behaviors, including interacting with /dev/watchdog for persistence and monitoring /proc/net/tcp for network activity.
